.TH PDFSPLIT 1 "December 2025" "pdfsplit 3.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pdfsplit \- Advanced PDF splitting, merging, and optimization tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pdfsplit
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIFILES\fR...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pdfsplit
is a powerful command-line tool for manipulating PDF documents. It supports
splitting PDFs by pages, granularity, bookmarks, or file size; merging multiple
PDFs; removing restrictions; reversing page order; exporting to PNG images;
extracting embedded images; and optimizing/compressing PDFs.
.PP
Input can be individual PDF files or directories (batch mode). When a directory
is specified, all PDF files in that directory are processed.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "Basic Options"
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Show version number and exit.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force
Force overwrite existing output files without prompting.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress non-error output.
.SS "Page Selection"
.TP
.BI \-p " PAGES" "\fR, " \-\-pages " PAGES"
Page specification string. Supports multiple formats:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Individual pages: "1,7,67"
.IP \(bu 2
Ranges: "1-10"
.IP \(bu 2
Open-ended ranges: "56-" (page 56 to end), "-10" (first 10 pages)
.IP \(bu 2
Combined: "1-5,10,20-25"
.RE
.TP
.BI \-g " N" "\fR, " \-\-granularity " N"
Split every N pages. Default is 1 (one output file per page).
.SS "Output Options"
.TP
.BI \-d " DIR" "\fR, " \-\-directory " DIR"
Output directory for split files. Default: pdf_out
.TP
.BI \-o " FILE" "\fR, " \-\-output " FILE"
Output file path. Required for \-\-merge, \-\-reverse, \-\-unlock, and
standalone \-\-optimize operations.
.TP
.BI \-\-prefix " PREFIX"
Custom prefix for output filenames. Default uses input filename.
.SS "Export Modes"
.TP
.B \-\-png
Export pages as high-quality PNG images instead of PDF files.
.TP
.BI \-\-dpi " DPI"
DPI (dots per inch) for PNG export. Default: 300. Valid range: 72-2400.
.TP
.B \-\-images
Extract embedded raster images from the PDF instead of page content.
.TP
.B \-\-info
Show PDF metadata (title, author, page count) and exit.
.SS "Advanced Operations"
.TP
.B \-\-merge
Merge multiple input PDFs into a single output file. Requires \-o/\-\-output.
.TP
.B \-\-reverse
Reverse page order of the input PDF. Requires \-o/\-\-output.
.TP
.B \-\-unlock
Remove restrictions (owner password protection) from the PDF.
Requires \-o/\-\-output. See \fBLEGAL DISCLAIMER\fR below.
.TP
.BI \-\-password " PASSWORD"
Password to decrypt user-password-protected PDFs. Used with \-\-unlock.
.TP
.B \-\-by\-bookmark
Split PDF at bookmark/TOC/chapter boundaries. Creates separate files for
each bookmarked section.
.TP
.BI \-\-max\-size " SIZE"
Split PDF when output exceeds the specified size limit. Useful for email
attachments or upload limits. Supports units: B, KB, MB, GB.
Examples: "10MB", "500KB", "1GB".
.SS "Optimization"
.TP
.B \-\-optimize
Optimize/compress PDF to reduce file size. Applies garbage collection,
stream compression, and optional metadata removal. Requires \-o/\-\-output
when used alone.
.TP
.BI \-\-quality " Q"
Image quality for optimization, 1-100. Default: 80. Lower values produce
smaller files with more compression artifacts.
.TP
.B \-\-keep\-metadata
Keep metadata during optimization. By default, metadata is removed.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS "Basic Splitting"
.TP
Split all pages (one PDF per page):
.B pdfsplit document.pdf
.TP
Extract pages 1-10:
.B pdfsplit document.pdf -p 1-10
.TP
Extract specific pages:
.B pdfsplit document.pdf -p 1,5,10-15
.TP
Split every 10 pages:
.B pdfsplit document.pdf -g 10
.TP
Batch process directory:
.B pdfsplit /path/to/pdfs/
.SS "PNG Export"
.TP
Export all pages as 300 DPI PNGs:
.B pdfsplit document.pdf --png
.TP
Export pages 1-5 as 600 DPI PNGs:
.B pdfsplit document.pdf -p 1-5 --png --dpi 600
.SS "Merging"
.TP
Merge multiple PDFs:
.B pdfsplit --merge a.pdf b.pdf c.pdf -o combined.pdf
.TP
Merge and optimize:
.B pdfsplit --merge *.pdf --optimize -o combined.pdf
.SS "Advanced Operations"
.TP
Reverse page order:
.B pdfsplit document.pdf --reverse -o reversed.pdf
.TP
Remove restrictions:
.B pdfsplit document.pdf --unlock -o unlocked.pdf
.TP
Decrypt with password:
.B pdfsplit encrypted.pdf --unlock --password "secret" -o unlocked.pdf
.TP
Split by bookmarks:
.B pdfsplit book.pdf --by-bookmark
.TP
Split by file size (10MB limit):
.B pdfsplit large.pdf --max-size 10MB
.SS "Optimization"
.TP
Basic optimization:
.B pdfsplit document.pdf --optimize -o smaller.pdf
.TP
Aggressive compression:
.B pdfsplit document.pdf --optimize --quality 60 -o compressed.pdf
.TP
Extract and optimize:
.B pdfsplit document.pdf -p 1-10 --optimize -o extract_optimized.pdf
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error (invalid arguments, file not found, processing error).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I pdf_out/
Default output directory for split files.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
